oc:kn_235ccb47 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating persuasive or keynote-style presentations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the Duarte Sparkline pattern for transformation narratives: alternate between 'What Is' (current pain) and 'What Could Be' (better future), with pattern breaks at 1/3 and 2/3 positions for engagement peaks." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The alternating tension-release pattern sustains audience engagement throughout longer presentations, proven by Nancy Duarte's research on effective presentations." .

oc:kn_2ae64b57 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing slide copy and headlines" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Map copywriting formulas to slide types: PAS for problem slides, AIDA for CTAs, FAB for features, Cost of Inaction for urgency, BAB for transformations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Formula-driven copy produces more persuasive, structured content that matches the emotional goal of each slide position in the deck arc." .

oc:kn_2bd2414c a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When regenerating or iterating on presentations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Re-running slide creation on the same topic will produce a different HTML file each time unless the same strategy, layout assignments, and copy formulas are explicitly specified." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Slide generation involves creative choices at multiple decision points (layout, formula, color, copy). Explicit parameterization is needed for reproducibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_471665f1 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When starting any new presentation creation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Select deck strategy (YC Seed, Sales Pitch, Product Demo, etc.) before creating individual slides, as the strategy dictates the emotion arc, slide count, and narrative structure." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Strategy-first design ensures the deck follows a proven narrative arc (e.g., curiosity→frustration→hope→confidence→trust→urgency) rather than assembling disconnected slides." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_923086c6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing individual slide layouts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not create slides with more than 6 bullet points, wall-of-text paragraphs, or unlabeled charts. Use feature grids (3-col), metric dashboards (4-col max), or big-number heroes instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Dense content slides overwhelm audiences. The layout-patterns reference provides 25 purpose-built layouts optimized for specific content types with appropriate animation classes." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ad6414cb a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any slide HTML structure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always wrap slide content in .slide-content divs and use the 16:9 aspect ratio container with letterboxing for desktop viewports." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The .slide-content wrapper constrains content within the safe area and enables proper flex centering. The 16:9 locked container ensures consistent presentation proportions across display devices." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

